spans.text: while mortals dream ; Cruel schemes they plan tonight , Mischief charms each pigmy sprite
while mortals dream ; Cruel schemes they plan tonight , Mischief charms each pigmy sprite
Thwart their marriage , fairy elves , Or scorn and hate
my elves begone , Impatient as my mind , Fly swift before the tardy moon , And leave even light behind
their baneful net , Round the sweetest minionet
from his bower , Plucks many a sweet and fatal flower
, he said , most loved and fair , The sweets which may with thee compare
Health over her cheek its roses threw , Diseases
— the blooming rose must die , For discord turned to harmony
to plant with care , What withering blasts had meant to spare , And with the auspicious day's return , In Hebe's breast it should be worn
She laughing tells her kinder sprite
Swift the friend of lovers flies , To steal the baneful cherished prise
